The paper deals with quantitative information flow analysis, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). It also involves the use of algorithms to construct a scheduler, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the effects of scheduling and observation on information leakage, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
